      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/63/5",
      "text": [
        " : «لاَ بَأْسَ إِنْ أَخَّرْتَ زِيَارَةَ اَلْبَيْتِ إِلَى أَنْ تَذْهَبَ أَيَّامُ اَلتَّشْرِيقِ إِلاَّ أَنَّكَ لاَ تَقْرَبُ اَلنِّسَاءَ وَ لاَ اَلطِّيبَ»."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2785 - Hisham ibn Salim narrated from Abu Abdullah (as), who said: \"There is no harm in delaying the visitation of the Kaaba (Tawaf al-Ziyara) until the days of Tashreeq have passed, except that you must not approach women or use perfume.\""
        ]
      }
